      <description>&lt;p&gt;slug: Three-js&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;a-brief-introduction-to-threejs&#34;&gt;A Brief Introduction to Three.js&lt;a href=&#34;#a-brief-introduction-to-threejs&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;&lt;svg class=&#34;h-4 w-4&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34;&gt;&lt;g fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34;/&gt;&lt;/g&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Three.js is an open-source JavaScript library built on top of the WebGL API. It wraps the complex operations of WebGL into easy-to-use APIs, making it convenient for developers to create 3D scenes and animations in web browsers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
